## Step 3: Disassemble `main` — find the entry point

```
(gdb) disas main
```

Key instructions:

```asm
0x0804886c <+18>:    movl   $0x0,(%esp)
0x08048873 <+25>:    call   0x80484b0 <time@plt>        ← time(NULL)
0x0804887b <+33>:    call   0x8048500 <srand@plt>       ← srand(time(0))
```

The PRNG is seeded but only used in the **failure path** (when key > 21).

```asm
0x080488b1 <+87>:    mov    $0x8048a85,%eax             ← "%u" format string
0x080488c1 <+103>:   call   0x8048530 <scanf@plt>       ← scanf("%u", &input)
```

Read the input as an unsigned integer.

```asm
0x080488ca <+112>:   movl   $0x1337d00d,0x4(%esp)       ← hardcoded constant
0x080488d5 <+123>:   call   0x8048747 <test>             ← test(input, 0x1337d00d)
```

We can verify the constant in GDB:

```
(gdb) x/s 0x8048a85
0x8048a85: "%u"
(gdb) p/d 0x1337d00d
$1 = 322424845
```

So `main` calls `test(input, 322424845)`.

